The first idea that comes to my mind is to create a `react Provider` that will serve not only as an enabler of the feature but also as the locator for the information.


```
const fn = (field: string) => {
  // get the description for the field somehow using the field name
};

<DescriptionProvider locatorFunction={fn}>
    <AutoForm .../>
</DescriptionProvider>
```

Then later on, the compatible fields can check whether the `DescriptionProvider` exists or not, and if so, use the provided function to retrieve the description.

